OL,4,Csocial media posts about match
OL,5,Cofficials
OL,7,FToday, the FA fined the club and also
OL,8,Fwarned them for misconduct.
OL,10,FThe club denied that the comments
OL,11,Fposted on social media constituted
OL,12,Fimproper conduct by implying bias and/
OL,13,For questioning the integrity of the
OL,14,Fmatch officials, and/or the video
OL,15,Fassistant referee and/or bringing the
OL,16,Fgame into disrepute.
OL,18,FBut an independent Regulatory
OL,19,FCommission found the charge to be
OL,20,Fproven following a hearing and imposed
OL,21,Fthe club's sanctions.
